Olivia F. Kirtley  Lead Independent Director, Papa John's International, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships66$267,723
Background

		Mrs. Olivia F. Kirtley served as the Chief Financial Officer and Vice President of Vermont American Corporation from 1991 to 2000. Mrs. Kirtley has extensive experience and insight, particularly in the areas of audit and corporate governance. She held several Management positions with Vermont American Corp., and from 1979 to 2000, she served as its Vice President of Finance, Treasurer and Director for Tax. She served with the international accounting firm of Ernst & ... Young. She serves as Vice Chairman of Community Foundation of Louisville Inc., The. She has been a Director at U.S. Bancorp since October 2006, Lancer Corp., since 1999 and Res-Care, Inc. since 1998. She has been a Director at Papa John's International Inc. since May 15, 2003 and has been its Lead Independent Director since October 27, 2016. After spending seven years with Ernst & Young, she was appointed firstly Vice-President, then Treasurer and then Chief Financial Officer of the Vermont American Corporation a position she held for 10 years. She serves as a Non-Executive Director of US Bancorp and Papa John's International, Inc. She is also the immediate past Chairman and President of the International Federation of Accountants and past council member of the International Integrated Reporting Council. Mrs. Kirtley serves as a Member of U.S. Banks local advisory board in Louisville, Kentucky. She serves as the Chairman of the AICPA Board of Examiners. She served as Chairman of American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) from 1998 to 1999. She is a Board Member of a number of charitable organizations, including The National Center for Family Literacy and SOZO International. She has been a Business Strategy Consultant on strategic and corporate governance issues for the past five years. She has been an Independent Non-Executive Director at Randgold Resources Limited since February 2, 2017. She has been a Director of Alderwoods Group, LLC since January 2, 2002. She is a Certified Public Accountant from the AICPA. Mrs. Kirtley was educated in the United States and holds a BS in Accounting degree from Florida Southern College and a Masters degree in Taxation from Georgia State University.Read Full Background




